The '''Apple Watch Series 3''' is the third-generation model of the [[Apple Watch]]. It was released on September 22, 2017.
== Overview == The main feature is the new built-in [[LTE (telecommunications)|LTE]] cellular connectivity, offering voice and data communication and Apple Music streaming. The watch comes with an electronic SIM card<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.theverge.com/2017/9/12/16270442/new-apple-watch-lte-announced-price-release-date-features|title=The new Apple Watch works without a phone|work=The Verge|access-date=2017-09-20}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2017/09/apple-watch-series-3-features-built-in-cellular-and-more/|title=Apple Watch Series 3 features built-in cellular and more|work=Apple Newsroom|access-date=2017-09-20|language=en-US}}</ref> and shares the same mobile number as the user's iPhone. Add-on plans start at $10/month from the four major US carriers.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://bgr.com/2017/09/12/apple-watch-3-cellular-plan-cost/|title=The Apple Watch Series 3 is going to cost you $10 per month, forever|last=Mills|first=Chris|date=2017-09-13|work=BGR|access-date=2017-09-20|language=en-US}}</ref>
==Hardware== Apple Watch Series 3 has a dual-core [[Apple S3]] processor that is 70% faster than the [[Apple S2]] and enables Siri voice responses. The cellular-capable watch has a red digital crown while the non-LTE version has a plain digital crown.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.macobserver.com/news/product-news/new-apple-watch-series-3-better-ever/|title=The New Apple Watch Series 3, Better Than Ever [Update] |date=2017-09-12|work=The Mac Observer|access-date=2017-09-20|language=en-US}}</ref> It has a built-in NFC chip which can be used for [[Apple Pay]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.techradar.com/news/apple-watch-compatible-gym-equipment-will-be-ready-by-september|title=Apple Watch-compatible gym equipment will be ready by September|work=TechRadar|access-date=2017-09-20|language=en}}</ref> Apple claims 18 hours of battery life.<ref name=":0" />
== Software == The Apple Watch Series 3 ships with [[watchOS]] 4, which has an updated Heart Rate app (including resting and recovery period monitoring), Workout app (with High Intensity Interval Training), as well as two-way data synchronization with GymKit-integrated cardio fitness equipment from companies such as Life Fitness, Technogym, Cybex, Schwinn, MS Artrix, Stair Master and Star Trac.<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://techcrunch.com/2017/09/12/apples-watch-3-rolls-out-heart-health-and-smart-fitness-features/|title=Apple’s Watch 3 rolls out heart health and smart fitness features|last=Buhr|first=Sarah|work=TechCrunch|access-date=2017-09-20|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2017/06/watchos-4-brings-more-intelligence-and-fitness-features-to-apple-watch/|title=watchOS 4 brings more intelligence and fitness features to Apple Watch|work=Apple Newsroom|access-date=2017-09-20|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2017/09/apple-watch-users-can-download-watchos-4-on-september-19/|title=Apple Watch users can download watchOS 4 on September 19|work=Ars Technica|access-date=2017-09-20|language=en-us}}</ref>
== Requirements == The Apple Watch Series 3 (GPS) requires an iPhone 5s or later with iOS 11 or later. The Apple Watch Series 3 (GPS + Cellular) requires an iPhone 6 or later with iOS 11 or later.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://support.apple.com/kb/SP766?locale=en_CA|title=Apple Watch Series 3 – Technical Specifications|website=support.apple.com|language=en|access-date=2017-12-11}}</ref>
